DataElement.preferredDefinition: A sample or part of a thing, or of several things, taken to demonstrate or to determine the character of the whole, e.g. a substance, or portion of material obtained for use in testing, examination, or study; particularly, a preparation of tissue or bodily fluid taken for examination or diagnosis.:An orderly arrangement. (from the American Heritage Dictionary):A subdivision of a particular kind of thing._Preceding all others in time or space or degree.:The magnitude of something in a particular direction, especially length or width or height.:A brief description given for purposes of identification; an identifying or descriptive marker that is attached to an object._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
